 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service on Friday said that light rain fell overnight on Thursday and is expected to continue along the south coast on Friday. "Some good news is that we can expect some temporary relief over the entire Eastern Cape next week," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. "With a constant onshore flow we can expect rain in the form of showers and thundershowers on and off between Sunday and Thursday. "However the long term forecast is dismal and below average rainfall is forecast until March 2020." Station Names 8 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 1.2 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 3.4 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 3.4 ARS Chatty NIL AWS Coega NIL AWSH Fettes Road * ARS Flower Reserve 0.8 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 2.6 ARS St Albans 3.0 AWS Uitenhage * Man Woodridge * Catchment  AWS Joubertina NIL ARS Kareedouw NIL Man Kareedouw NIL Man Kouga Dam NIL AWS Patensie *    Other Towns  AWS Addo NIL AWS Bisho/KWT NIL AWS Cape St Francis * AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL AWS George NIL AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown NIL AWS Henry`s Flats NIL AWS Joubertina NIL AWS Mossel Bay NIL AWS Mthatha 0.8 AWS Plettenberg bay NIL AWS Port Alfred NIL AWS Queenstown * * no contact 0.0 = Drops  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 